<inglise> Definitions </inglise>
<eesti> M&otilde;isted </eesti>
<inglise> For the purposes of this Directive, the following definitions shall apply: </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevas direktiivis kasutatakse j&auml;rgmisi m&otilde;isteid: </eesti>
<inglise> 1. working time shall mean any period during which the worker is working, at the employer's disposal and carrying out his activity or duties, in accordance with national laws and/or practice; </inglise>
<eesti> 1) t&ouml;&ouml;aeg - iga ajavahemik, mille jooksul t&ouml;&ouml;taja teeb t&ouml;&ouml;d, on t&ouml;&ouml;andja k&auml;sutuses ning tegutseb v&otilde;i t&auml;idab oma kohustusi koosk&otilde;las siseriikliku &otilde;iguse ja/v&otilde;i tavaga; </eesti>
<inglise> 2. rest period shall mean any period which is not working time; </inglise>
<eesti> 2) puhkeaeg - iga ajavahemik, mis ei ole t&ouml;&ouml;aeg; </eesti>
<inglise> 3. night time shall mean any period of not less than seven hours, as defined by national law, and which must include in any case the period between midnight and 5 a. m.; </inglise>
<eesti> 3) &ouml;&ouml;aeg - iga mitte v&auml;hem kui seitsme tunni pikkune siseriikliku &otilde;igusega m&auml;&auml;ratletud ajavahemik, mis peab igal juhul h&otilde;lmama ajavahemikku kesk&ouml;&ouml;st kuni kella viieni hommikul; </eesti>
<inglise> 4. night worker shall mean: </inglise>
<eesti> 4) &ouml;&ouml;t&ouml;&ouml;taja on: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) on the one hand, any worker, who, during night time, works at least three hours of his daily working time as a normal course; and </inglise>
<eesti> a) &uuml;helt poolt iga t&ouml;&ouml;taja, kes tavaliselt t&ouml;&ouml;tab &ouml;&ouml;ajal v&auml;hemalt kolm tundi oma igap&auml;evasest t&ouml;&ouml;ajast; ja </eesti>
<inglise> (b) on the other hand, any worker who is likely during night time to work a certain proportion of his annual working time, as defined at the choice of the Member State concerned: </inglise>
<eesti> b) teiselt poolt iga t&ouml;&ouml;taja, kes t&otilde;en&auml;oliselt t&ouml;&ouml;tab &ouml;&ouml;ajal teatud osa oma iga-aastasest t&ouml;&ouml;ajast, mis m&auml;&auml;ratletakse vastavalt asjaomase liikmesriigi valikule kas: </eesti>
<inglise> (i) by national legislation, following consultation with the two sides of industry; or </inglise>
<eesti> i) siseriiklikes &otilde;igusaktides p&auml;rast konsulteerimist t&ouml;&ouml;suhte pooltega; v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise> (ii) by collective agreements or agreements concluded between the two sides of industry at national or regional level; </inglise>
<eesti> ii) t&ouml;&ouml;suhte poolte vahel riiklikul v&otilde;i piirkondlikul tasandil s&otilde;lmitud kollektiivlepingutes v&otilde;i lepingutes; </eesti>
<inglise> 5. shift work shall mean any method of organizing work in shifts whereby workers succeed each other at the same work stations according to a certain pattern, including a rotating pattern, and which may be continuous or discontinuous, entailing the need for workers to work at different times over a given period of days or weeks; </inglise>
<eesti> 5) vahetustega t&ouml;&ouml; - iga vahetustega t&ouml;&ouml;korralduse meetod, mille puhul t&ouml;&ouml;tajad vahetuvad &uuml;hel ja samal t&ouml;&ouml;kohal &uuml;ksteise j&auml;rel vastavalt teatud mallile, kaasa arvatud rotatsioonimall, mis v&otilde;ib olla pidev v&otilde;i pausidega, tekitades t&ouml;&ouml;tajatel vajaduse t&ouml;&ouml;tada antud p&auml;evade v&otilde;i n&auml;dalate jooksul eri aegadel; </eesti>
<inglise> 6. shift worker shall mean any worker whose work schedule is part of shift work. </inglise>
