<inglise> Derogations may be made from Articles 3, 4, 5, 8 and 16 by means of collective agreements or agreements concluded between the two sides of industry at national or regional level or, in conformity with the rules laid down by them, by means of collective agreements or agreements concluded between the two sides of industry at a lower level. </inglise>
<eesti> Artiklitest 3, 4, 5, 8 ja 16 v&otilde;ib erandeid teha t&ouml;&ouml;suhte poolte vahel riiklikul v&otilde;i piirkondlikul tasandil s&otilde;lmitud kollektiivlepingute v&otilde;i lepingutega v&otilde;i, nendes etten&auml;htud korras, t&ouml;&ouml;suhte poolte vahel madalamal tasandil s&otilde;lmitud kollektiivlepingute v&otilde;i lepingutega. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States in which there is no statutory system ensuring the conclusion of collective agreements or agreements concluded between the two sides of industry at national or regional level, on the matters covered by this Directive, or those Member States in which there is a specific legislative framework for this purpose and within the limits thereof, may, in accordance with national legislation and/or practice, allow derogations from Articles 3, 4, 5, 8 and 16 by way of collective agreements or agreements concluded between the two sides of industry at the appropriate collective level. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid, kus ei ole seadusega etten&auml;htud s&uuml;steemi, mis tagaks t&ouml;&ouml;suhte poolte vahel riiklikul v&otilde;i piirkondlikul tasandil s&otilde;lmitavad kollektiivlepingud v&otilde;i lepingud k&auml;esolevas direktiivis k&auml;sitletud k&uuml;simustes, v&otilde;i liikmesriigid, kus on sel eesm&auml;rgil ja selle piires eriline &otilde;igusraamistik, v&otilde;ivad koosk&otilde;las siseriiklike &otilde;igusaktide ja/v&otilde;i tavadega lubada erandeid artiklitest 3, 4, 5, 8 ja 16 t&ouml;&ouml;suhte poolte vahel sobival kollektiivsel tasandil s&otilde;lmitud kollektiivlepingute v&otilde;i lepingute abil. </eesti>
<inglise> The derogations provided for in the first and second subparagraphs shall be allowed on condition that equivalent compensating rest periods are granted to the workers concerned or, in exceptional cases where it is not possible for objective reasons to grant such periods, the workers concerned are afforded appropriate protection. </inglise>
<eesti> Esimeses ja teises l&otilde;igus etten&auml;htud erandid on lubatud tingimusel, et k&otilde;nealustele t&ouml;&ouml;tajatele v&otilde;imaldatakse h&uuml;vituseks samav&auml;&auml;rse pikkusega puhkeajad v&otilde;i erandjuhtudel, kui objektiivsetel p&otilde;hjustel ei ole v&otilde;imalik niisuguseid puhkeaegu lubada, v&otilde;imaldatakse k&otilde;nealustele t&ouml;&ouml;tajatele asjakohane kaitse. </eesti>
