<inglise> The option to derogate from point 2 of Article 16, provided in paragraph 2, points 2.1. and 2.2. and in paragraph 3 of this Article, may not result in the establishment of a reference period exceeding six months. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva artikli l&otilde;ike 2 punktides 2.1 ja 2.2 ning l&otilde;ikes 3 etten&auml;htud v&otilde;imalus teha erand artikli 16 l&otilde;ikest 2 ei anna alust kehtestada kuuest kuust pikemat v&otilde;rdlusperioodi. </eesti>
<inglise> However, Member States shall have the option, subject to compliance with the general principles relating to the protection of the safety and health of workers, of allowing, for objective or technical reasons or reasons concerning the organization of work, collective agreements or agreements concluded between the two sides of industry to set reference periods in no event exceeding 12 months. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmeriikidel on v&otilde;imalus koosk&otilde;las t&ouml;&ouml;tajate turvalisuse ja tervisekaitse &uuml;ldiste p&otilde;him&otilde;tete j&auml;rgimisega lubada objektiivsetel, tehnilistel v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;korraldusega seotud p&otilde;hjustel kehtestada t&ouml;&ouml;suhte poolte vahel s&otilde;lmitud kollektiivlepingute v&otilde;i lepingutega v&otilde;rdlusperioodid, mille pikkus ei &uuml;leta &uuml;helgi juhul 12 kuud. </eesti>
<inglise> Before the expiry of a period of seven years from the date referred to in Article 18 (1) (a), the Council shall, on the basis of a Commission proposal accompanied by an appraisal report, re-examine the provisions of this paragraph and decide what action to take. </inglise>
